<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920117-0104</DOCNO><DOCID>920117-0104.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- UST Inc.:   Fourth-Quarter Net Income   Rose 21% to $66.3 Million</HL><DATE>01/17/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A7</SO><CO>   UST</CO><MS>CONSUMER NON-CYCLICAL (NCY)</MS><IN>BEVERAGES (BVG)DISTILLERS AND BREWERS, MAKERS OF ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGES (DST)EARNINGS (ERN)TOBACCO PRODUCTS (TOB)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>CONNECTICUT (CT)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   UST Inc., Greenwich, Conn., said its fourth-quarterearnings rose 21% on strong sales of its moist smokelesstobacco, wine and other products.   The tobacco and wine concern posted net income of $66.3million, or 30 cents a share, up from $54.7 million, or 24cents a share, a year earlier. Sales rose 17% to $235.5million from $201.5 million.</LP><TEXT>   For the year, UST's said its profit increased 19% to$265.9 million, or $1.18 a share, from $223.3 million, or 98cents a share, in 1990. All per-share figures reflect a2-for-1 stock split announced in December. Sales rose 19% to$907.3 million from $764.7 million.</TEXT></DOC>